# 08 — Server: GitHub / GitLab OAuth (full vertical)

**Status:** complete  
**Dependencies:** 07

## Objective
Implement **complete OAuth** for Git credentials in **one task** to avoid scattered half-finished auth: CSRF cookie, PKCE S256, callbacks, token storage, refresh-before-use (API_OVERVIEW §4b).

## Scope — In scope
- GET /auth/github, /auth/github/callback, /auth/gitlab, /auth/gitlab/callback
- HttpOnly SameSite=Lax cookie for state + PKCE verifier; validate on callback
- Store git_token, refresh_token, token_expires_at, git_provider, git_base_url on identity
- Proactive refresh when expired or within 5 minutes before use
- 503 when OAuth not configured

## Scope — Out of scope
- Agent-vendor OAuth (not v1 per PRODUCT)

## Acceptance criteria
- Integration tests: CSRF failure, happy path with mocked token exchange (no secrets in repo)
- Document required env vars in README or HOSTING pointer

## Completed / Notes (appended at task end)
- Implemented four OAuth routes with _rh_oauth cookie, PKCE S256, persistence
- GET /identities/:id/repositories refreshes OAuth tokens when near expiry
- PATCH /identities/:id resets OAuth metadata when git_token set/cleared manually
- Integration tests: crates/server/tests/oauth_integration.rs (DATABASE_URL); wiremock 0.5
- OpenAPI + README + HOSTING + CLI oauth subcommands + Web sign-in links

