IMPLEMENTATION DETAILS (oauth.rs)
---------------------------------
- Cookie name: _rh_oauth. Value: base64url(JSON { n: nonce, v: code_verifier }).
- State query param: base64url(JSON { n: nonce, i: identity_id }).
- CSRF: callback requires cookie.n == state.n.
- GitHub authorize: scope `repo`. GitLab: read_repository write_repository.
- GitHub token exchange/refresh: application/x-www-form-urlencoded + Accept: application/json
- GitLab token exchange/refresh: JSON body to /oauth/token
- Success redirect: REDIRECT_AFTER_AUTH + ?oauth_success=github|gitlab
- Failure redirects: oauth_error=csrf|provider|token_exchange|missing_code|missing_state (+ optional truncated oauth_message)
- maybe_refresh_oauth_git_token: only for git_provider oauth_github|oauth_gitlab; if token_expires_at within 5 min of now (or past), POST refresh; update DB and IdentityRow in memory
- OAUTH_COOKIE_SECURE adds Secure flag to Set-Cookie
- Incomplete env for one provider: from_env returns Err (fail fast) if partial triple (id/secret/uri) set

CONFIG ENV VARS (also in README)
---------------------------------
- REDIRECT_AFTER_AUTH (required for OAuth start when provider configured)
- GITHUB_CLIENT_ID, GITHUB_CLIENT_SECRET, GITHUB_REDIRECT_URI (all or none)
- GITLAB_CLIENT_ID, GITLAB_CLIENT_SECRET, GITLAB_REDIRECT_URI (all or none)
- GITLAB_BASE_URL optional (default https://gitlab.com)
- OAUTH_COOKIE_SECURE optional
- GITHUB_OAUTH_AUTHORIZE_URL, GITHUB_OAUTH_ACCESS_TOKEN_URL, GITLAB_OAUTH_* optional overrides (tests / advanced)

